Alpha, Eurobank Get Board Approval for Greek Bank Merger Plan

-- B y   M a r i a   P e t r a k i s
-- 
2011-09-20T14:48:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/alpha-eurobank-get-board-approval-for-greek-bank-merger-plan.html
Alpha Bank SA and  EFG Eurobank
Ergasias SA (EUROB)  both got board approval for a plan for Alpha to
acquire Eurobank to create the country’s biggest bank.  The legal merger of the two banks is expected to be
completed before the end of the year, according to a statement
filed by Athens-based Eurobank to the country’s bourse.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Maria Petrakis at 
 mpetrakis@bloomberg.net  